  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws and regulations targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to implement compliance programs, report suspicious activities, and conduct customer due diligence. Internationally, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering. Penalties can include significant fines and criminal prosecution for individuals and organizations involved in such activities.",
